xml.description:
Measure time of flight


The active rising edge timer is used to measure interval between setting SQ1 to 0 (electromagnet is turned off, and the ball starts dropping), and a falling edge event on SEN.



Connections.

  • 5V, GND for the relay
  • SQ1 to turn on/off the relay.
  • Detection switch between SEN and GND.




Description


the SEN input is an internally pulled up (to 3.3V via a 5K resistor) digital input capable of measuring time difference as well as analog level signals. When an input voltage goes from 0V to 3.3V , it is known as a rising edge. The opposite is called a falling edge.


When the relay is turned off, the ball drops and the timer immediately starts. It stops only when the ball hits the switch causing SEN to connect to GND causing a falling edge event.


You can calculate value of gravity using ﻿S=0.5∗g∗t2S = 0.5*g*t^2S=0.5∗g∗t​2​​﻿


Where S is the distance from the relay to the switch minus the diameter of the ball.
